long_description:
New limited releases from our friends at Seven Stills Distillery & Brewery are here! Sour beers, hazy IPAs and the taste of spiked Swedish Fish (yes) are both unexpected and totally expected from a brewery and distillery that’s unlike any other.

In case you haven’t heard, we’ve recently teamed up with the Bay Area distillery and brewery to create Seven Stills Nob Hill, a restaurant, bar and lounge specializing in whiskey and craft beer in our very own Stanford Court Hotel. Read more. 

Take a look at Seven Stills Brewery latest limited can releases.

Whiskey Sour

An India Pale Ale brewed with rye, lemon peel and cherry harkens to a summer afternoon of whiskey sours. Created in collaboration with Humble Sea Brewing from Santa Cruz, this sour IPA is something divine, with a husky IPA base that somehow manages to be both subtly sour and sweet. 

Rod & Reel

Two words: Swedish Fish. Indeed, this Imperial Red Ale is made with the gummy fish candy that has delighted this country since the 1950s. Made in collaboration with Libertine Brewing of San Luis Obispo, Rod & Reel has a beautiful color and an unmistakably candy-like finish without being overwhelming. A fat-free brew – just like the candy!

Twins

It’s Twins! This peach and apricot kettle sour is easy to drink though it rings in at nearly 6% ABV. With a can design based on the DeVito and Schwarzenegger film (but with their adorable apricot counterparts), you can’t help but feel fruity and fine while sipping on this kettle sour.

Eight Pounds Per BBL IPA

Eight Pounds is a double IPA that’s juicy and dank. It’s surprisingly fruity with tropical notes, made more complex with Mosaic hops. At just over 7% ABV, balance this beer out with an Impossible Burger or some Bang Bang ribs at Seven Stills Nob Hill.

Lifted Self

A barrel aged Neapolitan stout with chocolate, vanilla and strawberry, this powerful concoction is like a “milkshake” that you’ve spiked with only the finest stout beer. Sweet and smooth. 8.5% ABV. In addition to the base beer, Seven Stills has six variants of this stout, each with unique adjuncts added, made for release at different locations throughout the Bay Area. The brewery infused honey and graham cracker version is heading our way, and will be available only at Seven Stills Nob Hill.

Aside from the exciting new releases, Seven Stills Distillery and Brewery turns two years old this month! Celebrate along with Seven Stills on Sept. 8. More info on Eventbrite.

--

Stanford Court is a boutique hotel located in Nob Hill. Close to Chinatown, Union Square, and North Beach, Stanford Court Hotel offers free bike rentals to guests to make every part of San Francisco accessible.
